place.name: CULTS
place.gazetteerText: Cults.-- par. and hamlet (Cults Mill), mid. Fifeshire, 3½ miles SW. of Cupar, 2924 ac., pop. 704; contains sandstone and limestone quarries. Sir David Wilkie (1785-1841), the painter, was born in the manse. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
